@startuml
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "Pytest Runner" as Runner
participant "tests/conftest.py" as ParentConf
participant "test_post.py\n(Fixtures & Tests)" as TestFile
participant "create_post()\n(Helper Function)" as Helper
participant "FastAPI App" as App

== 1. Test Discovery & Fixture Lookup ==
Runner -> TestFile : Discover test requiring `created_post`
note right of Runner
  **Lookup Order:**
  1. test_post.py (Found!)
  2. tests/routers/conftest.py
  3. tests/conftest.py
end note

Runner -> TestFile : Analyze `created_post` dependencies
note right of TestFile: `created_post` requires `async_client`.\nPytest searches again and finds\nit in tests/conftest.py.

== 2. Dependency Injection & Setup ==
Runner -> ParentConf : Resolve `async_client`
ParentConf --> Runner : Yield injected `async_client`

Runner -> TestFile : Run `created_post` fixture
note right of Runner: Runner automatically passes\nthe `async_client` to the fixture.
activate TestFile

== 3. Helper Function Execution ==
TestFile -> Helper : await create_post("test post", async_client)
activate Helper

Helper -> App : async_client.post("/post", json=body)
note right of Helper: Passing `json=body` automatically\nsets Content-Type: application/json
activate App

App --> Helper : 200 OK (Post created)
deactivate App

Helper --> TestFile : response.json()
deactivate Helper

TestFile --> Runner : Return dictionary of the created post
deactivate TestFile

== 4. Test Execution ==
Runner -> TestFile : Run actual Test Function
note right of Runner: The test function now starts with\nthe `created_post` data ready to go!
TestFile -> TestFile : Perform test assertions

@enduml